Convert to improper fractions:
align*
3$\frac{1}{2}$ &= $\frac{7}{2}$ \\[6pt]
1\frac{1}{4} &= \frac{5}{4}
\end{align*}

Invert and multiply:
\[
\frac{7}{2} \div \frac{5}{4} = \frac{7}{2} \times \frac{4}{5} = \frac{7}{\cancelto{1}{2}} \times \frac{\cancelto{2}{4}}{5} = \frac{14}{5} = 2\frac{4}{5}
\]
